parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate to shift, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the overdrive light blinks or stays on
and the vehicle becomes difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause damage to the engine, transmission, and other components, leading to costly repairs, loss of power, and potential accidents.
Engine failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stranded, leading to accidents or inconvenience.

the vehicle stalls or becomes stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and hydraulic system can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stranded, leading to accidents or inconvenience.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical and sensor issues can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents or inconvenience.

symptoms: Excessive wear of front brake rotors and pads
pulsating or vibrating when brakes are applied
grinding noise when brakes are applied

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Deceptive business practices can cause financial harm to consumers, damage their credit, and lead to unsafe vehicles being sold to unsuspecting buyers.
